# The entire .lake/ tree is host-arch- and host-state-specific:
#   - .lake/build is darwin-arm64 olean output (wrong arch for the
#     linux container)
#   - .lake/packages/* contains Mathlib + dependency source code which
#     stage 1 will `lake update` + `lake exe cache get` to re-fetch
#     inside Docker
# Uploading it costs ~200 MB and stalls Depot's session token. The
# Docker build does NOT need any of it — it re-fetches sources and
# linux oleans from the Lean cache server during stage 1.
lean-workspace/.lake/

# Python venv / pyc
.venv/
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# Local-only files
*.log
.env*
benchmark_prove.py
try.py
